reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Goes great with Pacific blue iPhone!
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a thinner case to protect my new iPhone 12 Pro Max. A lot of the the thin cases look nice but don’t feel good in the hand for prolonged calls or viewing of the screen and most don’t offer drop protection. This case is a nice balance of thinness, sturdiness, and aesthetic. The blue color of this case matches nicely with the pacific blue iPhone. All the cutouts match up perfectly and the buttons have a nice response. Kudos to Torras for including neon yellow and orange buttons for this case. I may never use them but if I decide I want a change they’re available. The back of the case has a nice translucent black/grey back more towards charcoal grey. In regular room lighting I can just barely make out the apple logo. In sunlight you can see the apple logo through the back. Either way if you’re buying this to see your phonles blue through the back look elsewhere. It’s not a deal breaker for me and I kind of like that it takes on a different identity in different lighting. Now how this case feels is in another league of its own. I have tried cases from other brands and one twice what I payed for this case and it doesn’t feel as nice as this one does. It has the flat edges like the iPhone and is easy to hold. Decent grip and not too slippery like some have complained about. I think it feels great and it has a nice soft touch to it that is addicting to feel. You have to try it and see what I mean. Feels like silk. Lol. As for durability it looks like it can stand up to some abuse but only time will tell. As I use this case over the coming weeks I will adjust my rating accordingly. Right now I’ll give it a 4 for durability based on the rigid ness of the case. Lastly the there’s a decent lip around the phone and camera for protection and the case is easy on and easy off but fits snug so there’s no bulging out on the sides or anywhere on the phone. Drop protection should be good for medium drops. Love the blue/ grey contrast and out of 5 cases I tried on this phone this one is my favorite. Torras is a new brand to me and if the case holds up I will be buying for this and future phones. Great price to quality ratio. Hope this helps everyone.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best iPhone Case Owned
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I’m very impressed by this iPhone case. The texture and feel is great. It honestly makes you enjoy touching your phone. The raised protection of your camera is perfect. Set your phone down on a table and the camera lenses are safe from scratches and damage. I do suggest getting a camera protector for protection in your pocket or purse.The design is perfect. It’s sleek and slim so you don’t feel like you’re holding an iPhone 14 Plus in your hands that’s .6 inches larger than the iPhone 14. We either buy a Max or Plus for a larger phone/screen size. Cases can add to what we did not want: a large phone. This case does not do that. You really have no idea it’s there until you touch it. And as I said before, the feel and silicone texture of this case makes for a great feeling phone.As for the replacement buttons, I was very impressed by the ease of replacement and how well they fit. I thought these buttons were going to be the usual colored stickers. They’re actually very responsive and sturdy buttons you can interchange easily. Only thing I ask is if TORRAS has different color buttons besides yellow and red.Overall, after ordering 6 of the highly rated iPhone 14 cases, this one took the number 1 spot.

reviews.reviewTitle: Dünne, passgenaue Hülle. Rutschfest und top transparent.
reviews.reviewText: Die Hülle war gut und sicher verpackt. Mir hat die Schutzfolie für die Rückseite gefallen.Das verhindert Kratzer, die beim Transport entstehen können.Das Handy ging gut in die Hülle.Diese sitzt prima - stramm, aber nicht zu fest. Nichts wackelt. Du bekommst das Handy aber auch wieder aus der Hülle, ohne diese oder das Gerät zu beschädigen.Die Hülle ist schön dünn.Trotzdem habe ich das Gefühl, dass mein Handy sehr gut geschützt ist.Auch das Fotomodul auf der Rückseite ist durch den leicht erhöhten Rand geschützt.Überhaupt ist die Abdeckung der Bedienelemente sehr gut.Alle Drücker können sehr leichtgängig bedient werden, als wären sie überhaupt nicht abgedeckt.Lautsprecher und Ladebuchse sind perfekt ausgespart, alle meine Ladekabel passen.Kabellos laden funktioniert ebenfalls ohne Probleme. Ob sich dabei die Geschwindigkeit mit Hülle gegenüber ohne Hülle ändert, kann ich nicht sagen.Die Hülle liegt gut in der Hand. Es gibt keine scharfen Kanten oder Grate. Auch der Rand um das Kameramodul ist glatt.Dabei ist die Hülle nicht rutschig, sondern fasst sich sehr angenehm und griffig an.Die Transparenz ist super. Fingerabdrücke lassen sich, wie bei klaren Hüllen meist der Fall, nicht vermeiden.Ganz eben liegt das iPhone nicht auf dem Tisch (der Kamerabuckel, leider). Dieses Problem werden die meisten Hüllen haben.Klar, die Hülle ist neu. Muss ich sehen, wie das in einem Jahr aussieht.Zusammengefasst:Ein perfekte, dünne Schutzhülle, mit der das Handy angenehm und sicher in der Hand liegt, nach wie vor gut aussieht und problemlos bedient und geladen werden kann.
